All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary Exception Summary 
    Class Description
    BaseParameterPatterns
    Defines common path elements used in multiple REST controller classes.
    Beans
    Implements methods to satisfy dependencies on classes implemented outside of Spring and this application.
    FavoriteSkiResort
    Favorite Ski Resort joint entity in the database to join the User entity and SkiResort entity to allow a user to save a specific ski resort to their favorites for easy access.
    Friendship
    Friendship entity in the database to store information that allows users to friend each other.
    ImageNotFoundException
    Convenience class extending ResponseStatusException, for use when a request references a non-existing User's image.
    LocalFilesystemStorageService
    Simple implementation of StorageService, storing files in a directory specified in the application properties, further organized into subdirectories by specified portions of the generated filenames.
    Message
    Message entity to store information in regard to the messages a user may send to other people such as the sender/receiver, and the time it was created.
    MessageController
    REST Controller class for Message to receive parameter values taken from HTTP requests to their respective specified URL endpoints, and returning serialized JSON object results to HTTP responses.
    MessageRepository
    The MessageRepository extends the JpaRepository, which provides the CRUD (create, read, update, delete) functions, as well as providing the ability to delete records in batches.
    MessageService
    Service class for Message that will hold the business logic for the entity of saving, getting one or all instances of the entity, and deleting an instance of the entity.
    MimeTypeNotAllowedException
    Convenience class extending ResponseStatusException, for use when uploaded content is not on the whitelist.
    Post
    Post entity in the database to store information regarding the posts users can make to the community wall.
    PostController
    REST Controller class for Post to receive parameter values taken from HTTP requests to their respective specified URL endpoints, and returning serialized JSON object results to HTTP responses.
    PostRepository
    The PostRepository extends the JpaRepository, which provides the CRUD (create, read, update, delete) functions, as well as providing the ability to delete records in batches.
    PostService
    A Service class for the Post entity that participates in dependency injection, and performs more detailed methods for obtaining information for the PostController and PostRepository.
    PowdrApplication
    The main class for the Powdr webservice that allows the server to run through Spring.
    Preloader
    Class to preload data into the database.
    PreloadLauncher
    Configuration class to preload data into the database.
    SecurityConfiguration
    TODO Decoding the json web token
    ServiceLauncher
    Configuration class to launch the main server.
    SkiResort
    Ski Resort entity in the database to store information regarding a ski resort such as the ski resort name, and the latitude and longitude to pinpoint a specific ski resort, since multiple resorts can be on a single mountain.
    SkiResortController
    REST Controller class for SkiResort to receive parameter values taken from HTTP requests to their respective specified URL endpoints, and returning serialized JSON object results to HTTP responses.
    SkiResortRepository
    The SkiResortRepository extends the JpaRepository, which provides the CRUD (create, read, update, delete) functions, as well as providing the ability to delete records in batches.
    SkiResortService
    A Service class for the SkiResort entity that participates in dependency injection, and performs more detailed methods for obtaining information for the SkiResortController and SkiResortRepository.
    StorageException
    Convenience class extending ResponseStatusException, for use when an attempt to read, write, or delete a file fails with an IOException.
    StorageService
    Declares StorageService.store(MultipartFile), StorageService.retrieve(String), and StorageService.delete(String) methods for a file store.
    Trip
    Trip entity in the database to store information regarding a trip for a user such as the start time and end time of a trip to log the total number of days on the mountain, and distance traveled to see the total distance logged for a trip.
    TripController
    A RESTful Controller for the Trip entity that maps request data into JSON.
    TripRepository
    The TripRepository extends the JpaRepository, which provides the CRUD (create, read, update, delete) functions, as well as providing the ability to delete records in batches.
    TripService
    A Service class for the Trip entity that participates in dependency injection, and performs more detailed methods for obtaining information for the TripController and TripRepository.
    UploadConfiguration
    Declares a hierarchical set of properties, mapping to a corresponding hierarchy of application properties, all with the "upload." prefix.
    UploadConfiguration.FilenameProperties
    Encapsulates properties specifying the composition of filenames generated for files uploaded and stored in the file store.
    UploadConfiguration.FilenameProperties.TimestampProperties
    Encapsulates properties specifying the format and timezone context of timestamps incorporated into filenames generated for files uploaded and stored in the file store.
    User
    User entity in the database to store information in regards to various users such as: User ID, OAuthKey, their name, a biography section, and an image path for the user pictures.
    UserController
    REST Controller class for User to receive parameter values taken from HTTP requests to their respective specified URL endpoints, and returning serialized JSON object results to HTTP responses.
    UserNotFoundException
    Convenience class extending ResponseStatusException, for use when a request references a non-existing User entity instance.
    UserRepository
    The UserRepository extends the JpaRepository, which provides the CRUD (create, read, update, delete) functions, as well as providing the ability to delete records in batches.
    UserService
    User service class to be used and injected in the UserController.
